    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes the culture and style of the inhabitants of Oronga, a region of Easter Island. Orongo artwork is well known for its rock art carving, which contain an almost three-dimensional quality. There are numerous carvings of birdmen, commemorating the annual ceremony dedicated to selecting an island king.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
